# Bluecore Developer Mode

This application simulates the Bluecore template & widgets builder environment.

# How to use

1.  Find or Create the widget required for your template.
2.  Copy the Widget section represented with following commented code:

```html
<!-- Widget -->

// Your code

<!-- end widget -->

```

1.  Go to corresponding template in Bluecore.
2.  Paste the code inside the corresponding code block.
3.  Save & Close

## How to create a new widget

1.  Create a new file inside templates folder.
2.  Copy the source code of example.html file into the new one.
3.  Have FUN.

## How to handle css styles

You can find a folder in static (/static/css) that contains all the styles, you probably want to update or create a css file related to a widget inside widgets folder.
 
## How to index new widgets

1.  Open up index.html file in your code editor.
2.  Duplicate the elements involved in the link.
3.  Have FUN.

## How to run

1.  Run python [main.py](http://main.py)
2.  Go to [http://localhost:5000](http://localhost:5000)
3.  Have FUN

## How to install
1.  Run the following commands:

```html
pip install virtualenv
virtualenv venv
source venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt

```
